Cell[TextData[{
 "\tNow Bob performs a measurement on the two qubits ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["B", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ac12e88d-e14b-4a79-8855-86db7051b0fc"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["C", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "433ff7a7-f0e3-405d-af27-218b54663a25"],
 ", owned by Bob, in the Bell basis. The measurement will yield outcomes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "=", "0"}], ",", "1", ",", "2", ",", "3"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"d9ed1dfe-4c1a-42bb-9b65-ea47c93eccd9"],
 " and will collapse the total state vector into the corresponding term, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["S", "\[Mu]"], 
       TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
        "Ket"]}], ")"}], "A"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    SubscriptBox[
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Beta]", "\[Mu]"]},
      "Ket"], 
     RowBox[{"B", " ", "C"}]]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6fdc8cb1-4d10-470f-b5eb-d59cfa71bf83"],
 ", where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["S", "0"], "=", "I"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d8793ee7-28c3-4b60-8fb7-ec2e7186b860"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["S", "1"], "=", "X"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f8dbe51e-7187-4258-b26a-efc26d485fc3"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["S", "2"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "Y"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2ec4d70c-f979-4cc2-b91f-27af8f78a7b4"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["S", "3"], "=", "Z"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7cccf962-dc2e-4688-8835-9eb6cec56408"],
 ". The remaining task is for Bob to inform Alice of the outcome ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Mu]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c5520357-e7ae-41dc-a333-4b14a735d27e"],
 " so that Alice recover the desired state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fe3da5b2-2dca-4eb3-8988-34d1c524fb2a"],
 " by operating the inverse operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["S", "\[Mu]"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e711036e-ae44-4d19-9f64-b61ae780a0e2"],
 " on her qubit. The information regarding the measurement outcome amounts to \
two bits, and it requires only a classical channel for transmission."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1268048119,ExpressionUUID->"f27de986-e0ce-4047-8e66-9df2eff3b855"],

Cell["\<\
\tIn short, the quantum teleportation protocol consists of the following \
steps:\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->457023205,ExpressionUUID->"38c4e10a-ece9-40f5-bfcb-6080f5f0ea1c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Alice and Bob generate an entangled pair of qubits, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "de15b165-418c-4c9a-a7cb-23872f50a43f"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["B", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cce49455-909a-4bd0-94ae-a186374ebdfc"],
 ", and share the pair between them. This can be done anytime before the \
procedure actually starts. Bob prepares a quantum state to send in a separate \
qubit ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["C", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7d09e11e-75be-4850-80ef-1f71f8d5eac3"],
 "."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellID->1787484763,ExpressionUUID->"0b5586f4-4efe-4f30-acca-b17800c20080"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Bob makes a Bell measurement, i.e., the measurement in the Bell basis, on \
his two qubits ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["B", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "db71f067-e1b1-4140-a67d-9ae082f088f8"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["C", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c79a6fb3-cc40-479b-a677-2e3a16bf8413"],
 "."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellID->1107673858,ExpressionUUID->"27231c94-a04d-457c-b768-2e9df4ec5aa1"],

Cell["\<\
Bob sends the two-bit information regarding the measurement outcome to Alice \
through a classical communication channel.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellID->138795563,ExpressionUUID->"54dfa182-0c7a-4ab2-bc5b-aa028fc470b1"],

Cell["\<\
Alice operates a proper inverse operator to recover the desired quantum state.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellID->569786699,ExpressionUUID->"8101547a-20ac-426e-a834-034316a7420f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Preliminaries", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->775468120,ExpressionUUID->"2ccfe213-602b-43b7-b887-eed033fc3867"],

Cell["\<\
In the quantum teleportation protocol, two essential parts are sharing \
entanglement and performing the Bell measurement. Before we demonstrate an \
implementation of the quantum teleportation protocol, here we summarize \
quantum circuit models of the two tasks.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->214439197,ExpressionUUID->"7ac99715-5abd-48ba-93a2-d08372984e75"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Entangler Quantum Circuit", "Subsection",
 CellID->602024313,ExpressionUUID->"5ab5224b-4be5-4f2f-900e-83cb1d07f722"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<QuantumMob`Q3`\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[14]:=",
 CellID->56745906,ExpressionUUID->"12b318ad-dd88-42f4-9a51-602e07466b9c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To establish an entanglement between two qubits initially in a product \
state, one needs to interact them. In the quantum circuit model, the \
interaction is achieve by the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["CNOT"]], "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/CNOT", 
    "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "154d594b-2bd7-4850-bafa-07c729100490"],
 " gate. Specifically, one can use the feature of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["CNOT"]], "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/CNOT", 
    "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "63c3df3a-c603-4af5-a94c-5929c7593865"],
 " gate that copies the computational basis states of the control qubit to \
